quran[24]{c,v,t,f}:
  55,17,"Lord of the two Easts and Lord of the two Wests."
  55,18,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in?"
  55,19,"He merged the two waters{1}, converging together;",1:[Either the fresh water of rivers and the salty water of seas, or the waters of two different oceans.]
  55,20,"between them is a barrier which they do not overrun."
  55,21,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in?"
  55,22,"From them come out{1}pearls and corals.",1:[Qira’at: Nafie’, Abu Amr, Abu Ja’far and Ya’qub read it as: “From them are brought out pearls and corals.”]
  55,23,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in? "
  55,24,"His are the running ships, whose sails are raised{1}in the sea like banners{2}.",1:[Qira’at: Hamza and Shu’ba in one of his narrations read it as: “His are the running ships that raise their sails in the sea like banners.”],2:[The Arabic word used is <i>A’lām</i> which also means ‘tall mountains’.]
  55,25,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in?"
  55,26,"Everyone upon it{1}is bound to perish,",1:[The earth.]
  55,27,"and all that remains is your<sup>sg </sup>Lord’s Countenance, the Possessor of majesty and nobility."
  55,28,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in?"
  55,29,"Everyone in the heavens and the earth asks Him; every day He is bringing about a matter."
  55,30,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in?"
  55,31,"We{1}will attendto you<sup>pl </sup>, O two huge communities<sup>c </sup>.",1:[Qira’at: Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Ya’qub read it as: “He will attend to you,”],2:[The two types of responsible creatures: humans and <i>jinn</i>.]
  55,32,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in?"
  55,33,"O society of unseen beings and humans, if you<sup>pl </sup>can penetrate the bounds of the heavens and the earth then go ahead and penetrate; you will never penetrate except with authority{1}.",1:[The Qur’anic style involves leaving part of the meaning to be deduced by the listener; Ar-Rāzi and other exegetes said that this may mean ‘except with authority from God’, or ‘except with authority that you do not have’.]
  55,34,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in?"
  55,35,"Flares of fire, and brass{1}, will be sent upon you<sup>dl </sup>, and you will not find help<i>. </i>",1:[Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr and Rouh read it as: “Flares of fire and (of) brass…”]
  55,36,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in?"
  55,37,"And when the sky ruptures and becomes rose-colored like oil—"
  55,38,"so which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in?"
  55,39,"On that day neither any human nor unseen being{1}is asked about his misdeeds.",1:[The Arabic word used is <i>jānn</i> (the singular of jinn), which is an unseen being that is accountable for its actions..]
  55,40,"So which of your Lord’s marvels do you<sup>dl </sup>disbelieve in?"
